        <p class="text-sm text-war-text-dim">The project addresses significant water leakage issues on the upper floors (5th floor, kitchen, pantry, and living room of the 4th floor) due to porous areas on the horizontal roof membrane, bulkhead, and side walls. There are also cracks and water leaks in the basement area near the meters and electrical closet. Due to time and temperature constraints, and the presence of asbestos, a temporary roof (Phase 1) is being installed, which will serve as the first layer for a permanent roof to be installed in the spring.</p>
